cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it proposes a self-supervised learning approach for medical image analysis. The paper also leverages multiple imaging modalities, which suggests that it may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. The use of neural networks for representation learning and fine-tuning on downstream tasks suggests that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper employs the Sinkhorn operator, which is a tool from optimal transport theory, suggesting that it may also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
